<HL>
   Business Brief -- Legg Mason Inc.:
   Net Rose 4% in 1st Period
   On 1.2% Revenue Increase
</HL>
<DATE>
07/20/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   LM
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Legg Mason Inc., propped by gains in its investment
advisory business, reported a 4% rise in fiscal first-quarter
profit.
   The regional brokerage firm, based in Baltimore, said net
income for the quarter ended June 30 rose to $3.2 million, or
37 cents a share, up from $3.1 million, or 36 cents a share,
a year earlier.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Revenue for the period rose 1.2% to $60.1 million from
$59.4 million. Investment advisory revenue rose 19% as assets
under management rose to more than $8.5 billion, offsetting a
drop in commission revenue.
</TEXT>
